You are working on ambiguity — a deterministic prompt analysis tool.

## Key facts

- Dual implementation: Python (`src/ambiguity/`) + TypeScript (`ts/src/`)
- Both must stay in sync (same modules, same logic)
- Zero LLM calls — all analysis is regex + dict + arithmetic
- Federation UDL bridge is optional try/import

## When editing

1. Run tests after changes: `pytest tests/` (Python) or `cd ts && npm test` (TS)
2. Keep both implementations in sync — if you add a verb to one taxonomy, add it to the other
3. Check `AGENTS.md` for project conventions and handoff instructions
4. Check `QUICKSTART.md` for install and usage patterns

## Project files to know

- `src/ambiguity/containers.py` — verb taxonomy (Python)
- `ts/src/containers.ts` — verb taxonomy (TypeScript)
- `src/ambiguity/scoring.py` — scoring formula
- `ts/src/scoring.ts` — scoring formula (mirrors Python)
- `src/ambiguity/parser.py` — token extraction logic
- `AGENTS.md` — full agent guide
